  "prompt": "Who sings a song titled \"Home\"?",
  "response": "Several artists have released songs titled \"Home,\" each with their own unique style and interpretation. Here are some of the most notable ones:\n\n1. **Edward Sharpe & The Magnetic Zeros**  \n   - **Release Year:** 2009  \n   - **Genre:** Indie Folk  \n   - **Description:** A beloved anthem celebrating community and togetherness, known for its catchy chorus and harmonious vocals.\n\n2. **Phillip Phillips**  \n   - **Release Year:** 2012  \n   - **Genre:** Pop Rock  \n   - **Description:** Won \"American Idol\" Season 11, featuring an uplifting melody that emphasizes finding one's place and sense of belonging.\n\n3. **BTS**  \n   - **Release Year:** 2019  \n   - **Genre:** K-Pop  \n   - **Description:** A heartfelt song that expresses longing for home and comfort, reflecting themes of belonging and personal growth.\n\n4. **Michael Bubl\u00e9**  \n   - **Release Year:** 2005  \n   - **Genre:** Pop Jazz  \n   - **Description:** A smooth, emotional rendition about missing home and loved ones, showcasing Bubl\u00e9's signature vocal style.\n\n5. **Martin Garrix feat. Bonn**  \n   - **Release Year:** 2018  \n   - **Genre:** EDM  \n   - **Description:** An electronic dance track that combines energetic beats with lyrical themes of returning to one's roots.\n\n6. **Taylor Swift**  \n   - **Release Year:** 2012  \n   - **Genre:** Country Pop  \n   - **Description:** A track from her album \"Red,\" reflecting on past relationships and the feeling of returning home emotionally.\n\nEach of these songs titled \"Home\" offers a different musical experience, so the best one for you might depend on your personal taste in music genres and themes.\n\nIf you're looking for a specific \"Home\" song, providing more details like the genre or the context can help narrow it down!",
